   We recognize, in fact, that these components of momentum agree with
   those of classical mechanics for velocities which are small compared to
   that of light. For large velocities the momentum increases more rapidly
   than linearly with the velocity, so as to become infinite on
   approaching the velocity of light.

   If we apply the last of equations (43) to a material particle at rest (
